    "client_msg_id": "b86dcd90-a7bf-4234-a0bc-dfdd2eb561da",
    "type": "message",
    "text": "Notebook vs. shell: (1) different visual presentation, with notebooks emphasizing history, (2) most notebooks support graphical output display.\n\nShell vs. REPL: what we call \"shell\" is both a REPL and a language designed for a REPL interface to the OS (plus OS scripting).\n\nI have seen many attempts to replace the shell by some other language's REPL, by providing a more concise interface to OS services in that other language. LISPers seem particularly tempted by this.",
    "user": "UJBAJNFLK",
    "ts": "1664258645.976549",
    "team": "T5TCAFTA9",
    "blocks": [
      {
        "type": "rich_text",
        "block_id": "5uJg",
        "elements": [
          {
            "type": "rich_text_section",
            "elements": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Notebook vs. shell: (1) different visual presentation, with notebooks emphasizing history, (2) most notebooks support graphical output display.\n\nShell vs. REPL: what we call \"shell\" is both a REPL and a language designed for a REPL interface to the OS (plus OS scripting).\n\nI have seen many attempts to replace the shell by some other language's REPL, by providing a more concise interface to OS services in that other language. LISPers seem particularly tempted by this."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ],
